<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="511" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1586,1791]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1622,1647]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Presutural spots fused and extended anteriorly on to postpronotum to beyond the inner anterior seta; postsutural dorsocentrals 4; mid femur with 2 preapical setae; mid tibia with 2 posterior setae; costal spine not distinct; first abdominal segments yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1586,1791]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1730,1755]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Notes.</emphasis>
